issues.body:
The two `data` dicts passed to a pipeline have different behaviours


This makes some components run twice

```python
pipe_from_file.run(
    {"prompt_builder": {"query": query}, 
      "retriever": {'query': 'What is the capital of France?'}
      }
  )
```

whereas if we explicitly pass the `None` values to some inputs makes the job of the Pipeline `run()` method easier

```python
pipe_from_file.run(
    {"prompt_builder": {"query": query}, 
      "retriever": {
          'filters': None, 
          'query': 'What is the capital of France?', 
          'scale_score': None, 
          'top_k': None}
      }
  )
```

On way to solve this is to overwrite the `data`dict at the beginning of the `run` with all the parameters default/None parameters needed for a component.

